          "notes": "- Any 3-Ping + [red]Red Orb Ping[/red] triggers <strong>Dual Blades</strong> (Core Passive) for 5 seconds:\n- During <strong>Dual Blades</strong> performing Basic Attacks will cause Lotus to attack with two blades, dealing increased damage\n- <strong>Dual Blades</strong> lasts long enough to complete two enhanced Basic Attack strings\n\n- It's recommended to use a [blue]Blue Orb 3-Ping[/blue] to activate <strong>Dual Blades</strong>:\n- The [blue]Blue Orb 3-Ping[/blue] will add Fire DMG to the extra Basic Attacks from the Core Passive\n- If performed in quick succession, the [blue]Blue Orb 3-Ping[/blue]'s buff will last for the whole duration of <strong>Dual Blades</strong>\n\n- Core Passive details:\n- Can only be activated if the [red]Red Orb Ping[/red] is performed within 4 seconds after a 3-Ping\n- Lotus will not generate new Signal Orbs while <strong>Dual Blades</strong> is active\n- Pinging Orbs during <strong>Dual Blades</strong> doesn't result in higher damage\n\n- Advanced techniques:\n- Using an Extreme Dodge to trigger Matrix can simplify the activation of <strong>Dual Blades</strong>, requiring only a Signal Orb of any color and a [red]Red Orb Ping[/red]\n- The Fire DMG dealt when under the effects of a [blue]Blue Orb Ping[/blue] cannot critically strike, but will ignore enemy armor\n- Lotus performs a free [red]Red Orb 3-Ping[/red] automatically when switched in, allowing a quick activation of <strong>Dual Blades</strong> with any additional [red]Red Orb Ping[/red] within 4 seconds\n- The extra Fire DMG from a [blue]Blue Orb Ping[/blue] is applied as an additional damage instance to every individual hit: \n- During <strong>Dual Blades</strong> the extra Fire DMG will trigger twice for every attack\n- Attacks that hit multiple times (like a [red]Red Orb Ping[/red]) are much stronger while under the effects of a [blue]Blue Orb Ping[/blue]",
