          "bio": "This unit's official title is Model S, Number 9. While this YoRHa member possesses offensive capabilities, he specializes in survey missions—and is particularly skilled at information gathering and hacking.",
          "effect": "<strong>Core Passive — [blue]At least 50 Overclock Energy + Any 3-Ping[/blue]</strong>\nGains [red]Overclock Energy[/red] at the start of the battle. During a 3-Ping, if there is sufficient [red]Overclock Energy[/red], consumes [red]Overclock Energy[/red] to generate [red]Overclock Indicator[/red] of the corresponding color (up to 1) on the right of the Signal Orb bar. [red]Overclock Energy[/red] regenerates over time. \n- Gains [red]100 Overclock Energy[/red] at the start of the battle. \n- During a 3-Ping, if there is more than [red]50 Overclock Energy[/red], consumes [red]50 Overclock Energy[/red] to gain [red]Overclock Indicator[/red]. \n- [red]Overclock Energy[/red] regenerates by 20 every second (max 100).\n\n<strong>Core Passive — [blue]Ping Overclock Indicator[/blue]</strong>\nTapping the [red]Overclock Indicator[/red] will consume all orbs of the same color and summon a POD to unleash multiple projectiles that deal Physical DMG (pinging [red]Overclock Indicator[/red] is not considered a ping). If the [red]Overclock Indicator[/red] effect pings more than 3 Signal Orbs, gains a number of random Signal Orbs equal to the excess number of orbs pinged. When 9S leaves the field, reduces his swap cooldown according to how many times [red]Overclock Indicator[/red] has been triggered. \n- Deals [red]100% / 200% / 300%[/red] Physical DMG in total based on the number of orbs pinged. \n- Each [red]Overclock Indicator[/red] triggered reduces his swap cooldown by [red]1[/red]s, up to [red]4[/red]s.",
