          "bio": "The frame of Pulao, one of the Dragon Children, is not made from conventional components but has been carefully adapted to fit her M.I.N.D., allowing her to make the most of her unusually strong powers.",
          "effect": "<strong>Core Passive — [blue]Whenever catching Dragon Axe[/blue]</strong>\nWhenever Pulao: Dragontoll catches Dragon Axe, she will throw it again, dealing the same effect as [red]Spirit Blade: Dragon Throw[/red].\n\n<strong>Core Passive — [blue]Tap Basic Attack / Ping any orb[/blue]</strong>\nBasic Attacks or pinging orbs will generate [red]Dragon Force[/red]. \n- Basic Attacks generate [red]3 Dragon Force[/red]. \n- [red]3/6/12 Dragon Force[/red] will be generated based on the number of orbs pinged. \n- Up to [red]50 Dragon Force[/red] can be stored.\n\n<strong>Core Passive — [blue]Ping Yellow Orb + Pina Red Orb[/blue]</strong>\nIf Pulao: Dragontoll catches Dragon Axe when performing her Red/Blue/Yellow Orb skill, consumes Dragon Force to unleash [red]Dragon Force Combo[/red], with which tapping the Basic Attack button repeatedly will perform a follow-up combo that deals Physical DMG. While performing Dragon Force Combo and the follow-up combo, Pulao: Dragontoll gains Super Armor and Extra DMG Reduction. \n- Dragon Force Combo consumes [red]25 Dragon Force[/red]. \n- If Pulao: Dragontoll catches Dragon Axe when performing her Red/Blue/Yellow Orb skill and casts [red]Dragon Force Combo[/red], tapping the Basic Attack button repeatedly can perform a follow-up combo that deals [red]1200% / 1200% / 1200%[/red] Physical DMG in total. \n- While performing [red]Dragon Force Combo[/red] and the follow-up combo, Pulao: Dragontoll gains Super Armor and [red]80%[/red] Extra DMG Reduction.",
          "priority": "Increases Physical DMG dealt by [red]15%[/red] and Base DMG of [red]Signature - Spirit Blade Dance[/red] by [red]25%[/red]. CRIT Rate of [red]Spirit Blade: Falling Stars[/red] increases by [red]30%[/red] for every [red]Dragon Force Combo[/red] cast. (Can be stacked up to [red]2[/red] times)",
