              "summary": "- Quickly accumulate Energy in order to cast Signature Move and enter Thunder Burst Form\n- Hold Basic Attack to perform <strong>Revving Charge</strong>, slowing gaining Energy over time\n- Against an incoming attack, tap Dodge without a movement input to perform Arm Block, negating damage and gaining half the required Energy\n- Perfectly time the tap Dodge to perform Perfect Arm Block and immediately max out the Energy gauge\n\n- In Thunder Burst Form, the Signal Orb in Orb Slot 1 is replaced with an Overload Orb, and a red gauge will appear on-screen indicating the time remaining before Thunder Burst Form ends\n- When an orb is marked and appears within the Overload Orb, ping the Overload Orb to cast Thunderous Fury\n- During Thunderous Fury, hold Basic Attack to cast the Thunderclap Strike follow-up attack and gain 1 Engine Point, displayed as a red arc surrounding the Signature Move icon\n\n- With at least 1 Engine Point, cast Skull Crush by tapping Signature Move again or allowing Thunder Burst Form to expire\n- All Engine Points will be consumed to boost the damage of Skull Crush\n\n- During <strong>Revving Charge</strong>, Arm Block will be performed automatically to defend against incoming attacks without needing to manually tap Dodge\n- Perfect Arm Block can still be performed during Revving Charge, but requires perfectly timing the tap Dodge\n\n- Perfect Arm Block will trigger Matrix if it is available, and grant 1 random Signal Orb\n\n- Only 1-Ping Signal Orbs can be marked by the Overload Orb, 2-Ping and 3-Ping Orbs cannot be marked\n- Keeping two sets of 3-Pings in the Signal Orb bar ensures that the next Signal Orb generated will always be a 1-Ping available for Overload Orb marking\n\n- Thunderous Fury does not have Super Armor, despite its Thunderclap Strike follow-up having Super Armor\n\n- While in Thunder Burst Form, casting any 3-Ping and then holding Basic Attack will refresh Thunder Burst Form's duration back to the full time limit",
