          "memory": "Build:Decryptor",
          "bio": "Vice-captain of the Engineering Force. Since she is a programming expert, the core configurations of her frame are geared more toward a technician. However, this doesn't mean that she's not capable of combat—her stage is far beyond the battlefield in the physical world.",
          "effect": "<strong>Fraudulent Frequency </strong>\nDecryptor can only gain and ping Red or Yellow Orbs when she is not in [red]Analysis Mode[/red]. She gains infinite Blue Orbs and can only ping Blue Orbs when in [red]Analysis Mode[/red].\n\n<strong>Hacking — [blue]Any 3-Ping or QTE[/blue]</strong>\n3-Pings and QTEs will inflict a [red]Hacked Mark[/red] on the first target hit for [red]10s[/red]. When the hacked target takes damage, Decryptor will restore [red]30 Signature Energy[/red] every second.\n- There can only be 1 [red]Hacked Mark[/red] on the battlefield. When the hacked target is taken down, the [red]Hacked Mark[/red] will spread to the nearest target with its duration reset.\n\n<strong>Programming Stack — [blue]Ping Orb[/blue]</strong>\nDecryptor gains [red]1 Computing Point[/red] for each orb pinged, storing up to [red]9 Computing Points[/red] in total. After a 3-Ping, Decryptor will overload her computing power temporarily. During her next 1-Ping or 2-Ping, tap Signature to spend [red]15 Signature Energy[/red], boosting the ping's damage to a 3-Ping's and gaining [red]3 Computing Points[/red].\n\n<strong>Stress Integration —[blue]Ping Stress Orb[/blue]</strong>\nGains [red]1 Stress Orb[/red] after obtaining [red]9 Computing Points[/red], max 1 [red]Stress Orb[/red] in total. Upon pinging the [red]Stress Orb[/red], Decryptor will leap up and summon the Grizzly Chomp, bombing the target and dealing [red]1000%[/red] Dark DMG upon landing plus [red]150%[/red] Extra DMG to [red]Equilibrium Field[/red]. She gains Super Armor and 50% DMG Reduction during so.\n- Pinging the [red]Stress Orb[/red] when Decryptor [red]is not in Analysis Mode[/red] will restore [red]75 Signature Energy[/red].\n\n<strong>Iterative Glitch — [blue]Incoming Grizzly Chomp + Tap Basic Attack or Signature[/blue]</strong>\nPing Combo 3 will summon Grizzly Chomp to fly toward Decryptor. She can either perform an Extreme Dodge to trigger the Matrix, or knock Grizzly Chomp away with Grizzly Paws or Grizzly Stomp for a follow-up joint attack.\n- Grizzly Chomp will deal [red]200%[/red] Dark DMG  if knocked away by Grizzly Paws.\n- Grizzly Chomp will deal [red]50%[/red] Dark DMG and restore [red]60 Signature Energy[/red] to Decryptor if knocked away by Grizzly Stomp when Decryptor [red]is not in Analysis Mode[/red]. If she is in [red]Analysis Mode[/red], Grizzly Chomp will deal [red]50%[/red] Dark DMG and extend [red]Analysis Mode[/red] for [red]2s[/red].",
          "priority": "ATK increases by 10%. Base DMG of Signal Orbs and Stress Orbs increases by 30%. When Teddy: Decryptor enters the battlefield while she is not in Analysis Mode, she will enter Analysis Mode automatically and gain 40 Analysis Points if she has full Signature Energy. Otherwise, she gains 100 Signature Energy.",
