                  "description": "<strong>Fortify - [blue]Not Moving + Press and Hold Dodge[/blue]</strong>\nBridget: Ardeo blocks the attack with her Tactical Tonfas. She cannot move or restore Dodge Gauge during so, and Dodge Gauge is consumed based on the DMG prevented and her max HP when hit (Dodge Gauge is not consumed on a precise block).\n-  If there is enough Dodge Gauge, Bridget: Ardeo is immune to the hit upon a successful block. Otherwise, she gains [red]50%[/red] DMG Reduction for the hit instead.\n- After a successful block, recovers [red]100 Fortification Points[/red], and an additional [red]50 Fortification Points[/red] on a precise block. Bridget can have up to [red]300 Fortification Points[/red].\n- When she enters the battlefield, restores her [red]Fortification Points[/red] to [red]150[/red] if it is below [red]150[/red].\n\n<strong>Discharge</strong>\nAfter being thrown, the Energy Shield will stay on the field and gain 6 Durability.\n-  Flying Sparks and Whirling Strike can launch the Energy Shield, recovering [red]50 Fortification Points[/red] and consuming 1 Durability.\n- The Energy Shield can trigger Detect and Counter and Fortify, consuming 1 Durability.\n- Triggers available Matrix upon an Extreme Dodge on the Energy Shield.\n- When Bridget: Ardeo recovers the Energy Shield, she receives a shield equal to [red]30%[/red] of her Max HP and gains 1 Blue Orb.\n\n<strong>Effect: Ignition</strong>\nCombustible: Every [red]250[/red] Combustible Charges will add [red]1[/red] Combustible stack, up to 20 stacks.\nIgnition: Ignited units take Ignition DMG equal to [red]Ignition stacks x30%[/red] (Tank Skills will not be triggered) every second for 10s.\n- The subsequent unit will inherit the Combustible/Ignition status of the last unit on the battlefield upon its death.",
