          "memory": "Build:Fulgor",
          "bio": "Following the style of the Yata human era, this unit is specifically designed for extended combat operations. Equipped with high-performance plasma armatures in its arm structure and rear-mounted mechanical arms, it can unleash devastating kinetic energy in an instant.",
          "effect": "<strong>Vortex Absorption</strong>\nBasic Attack only grants Red or Yellow Orbs. Ping Red or Yellow Orbs to gain [red]Heartflow[/red].\n\n<strong>Divine Teaching</strong>\nYata can enhance herself through [red]Heartflow[/red].\n- Yata is in the [red]Void Realm[/red] upon entering the battlefield. After gaining [red]90 Heartflow[/red], she will enter the [red]Sanctuary Realm[/red] and gains an [red]Esoteric Orb[/red], granting her Super Armor when casting [red]Thunder Outflux - Night Raid[/red].\n- After gaining [red]60 Heartflow[/red] in the [red]Sanctuary Realm[/red], Yata will enter the [red]Epiphany Realm[/red] and gain an [red]Esoteric Orb[/red] and a [red]10%[/red] ATK Bonus. After that, every [red]30 Heartflow[/red] will grant an [red]Esoteric Orb[/red].\n-  Gaining an [red]Esoteric Orb[/red] will enhance the existing [red]Esoteric Orbs[/red].\n- Upon exiting the battlefield, Yata will reenter the [red]Void Realm[/red] and clear her [red]Heartflow[/red], [red]Illumination[/red], and [red]Esoteric Orbs[/red].\n\n<strong>Mirror Return — [blue]Not Moving + Tap Dodge to Block Successfully + Tap Basic Attack[/blue]</strong>\nTap Dodge without moving the joystick to perform a Block. After a successful Block, tap Basic Attack to counterattack, dealing [red]540%[/red] Lightning DMG. If the Block triggers a Matrix, [red]Mirror Return[/red] will additionally restore a set of Signal Orbs.\n\n<strong>Night Raid — [blue]With Illumination + Press and Hold Basic Attack[/blue]</strong>\nYata gains [red]Illumination[/red] by casting [red]Esotericism: Slash[/red]. [red]Illumination[/red] can stack up to 2 times. With [red]Illumination[/red], press and hold Basic Attack to spend all [red]Illumination[/red] stacks and cast [red]Night Raid[/red], dealing damage based on [red]Illumination[/red] stacks spent.\n- [red]Night Raid – Patrol[/red] deals [red]240% / 400%[/red] Lightning DMG, then followed by [red]Night Raid – Snatch[/red]. When there are Ice Spikes, deals [red]216% / 360%[/red] Glaciation DMG instead.\n- [red]Night Raid – Snatch[/red] deals [red]360% / 600%[/red] Lightning DMG every second. When casting it, Yata will automatically block incoming attacks at the cost of Dodge Gauge value and gain 1 Signal Orb every [red]1.5s[/red]. Release Basic Attack to cast [red]Night Raid – Halt[/red]. When there are Ice Spikes, deals  [red]288% / 480%[/red] Glaciation DMG every second.\n- Channeling [red]Night Raid – Snatch[/red] for more than 1s to accumulate Glaciation Gauge value over time and at an increasing speed. After 1s, gains [red]100[/red] Glaciation Value every second. After 2s, gains [red]200[/red] Glaciation Value every second. After 4s, gains [red]250[/red] Glaciation Value every second.\n- [red]Night Raid – Halt[/red] deals [red]600% / 1000%[/red] Lightning DMG. Gains [red]10[/red] Signature Energy after casting it. When there are Ice Spikes, deals [red]540% / 900%[/red] Glaciation DMG instead.\n\n<strong>Effect: Glaciation</strong>\nSome of the skills can fill the [red]Glaciation Gauge[/red]. When the gauge is full, consume it to cast [red]Arctic Ice[/red], dealing Glaciation DMG and gaining [red]Arctic Ice Layers[/red]. Casting certain skills will consume all [red]Arctic Ice Layers[/red] to form [red]Ice Spikes[/red], dealing Glaciation DMG to nearby enemies. While [red]Ice Spike[/red] persist, dealing Glaciation DMG will trigger [red]Ice Accumulation[/red], which deals additional Glaciation DMG and gains [red]Glaciation Value[/red]. When [red]Ice Spikes[/red] expire, they will trigger [red]Ice Burst[/red] to deal Glaciation DMG based on the current [red]Glaciation Value[/red].  The [red]Glaciation Gauge, Arctice Ice Layers, Ice Spikes[/red], and [red]Glaciation Value[/red] can transfer to the next character with Effect: Glaciation.\n- At [red]100 Glaciation Value[/red], casts [red]Arctice Ice[/red] to deal [red]100%[/red] Glaciation DMG and generate [red]1 Arctic Ice Layer[/red]. Max [red]10 Layers[/red].\n- When having more than [red]0 Arctic Ice Layers[/red], certain skills can consume all [red]Arctic Ice Layers[/red] to form [red]Ice Spikes[/red], dealing [red]180%[/red] Glaciation DMG. When forming [red]Ice Spikes[/red], every [red]1 Arctic Ice Layer[/red] consumed will extend their duration by [red]1[/red]s.\n- While [red]Ice Spikes[/red] persist, dealing Glaciation DMG will trigger [red]Ice Accumulation[/red], which deals [red]100%[/red] Glaciation DMG in a large area and gains [red]100 Glaciation Value[/red]. This can only trigger [red]once[/red] every [red]0.25[/red]s.\n- When [red]Ice Spikes[/red] expire, it will trigger [red]Ice Burst[/red] to deal [red]100%[/red] Glaciation DMG in a large area. For every [red]100 Glaciation Value[/red] owned, the Base DMG of [red]Ice Burst[/red] increases by [red]9%[/red], up to [red]10000 Glaciation Value[/red].",
          "priority": "ATK increases by 10%. While in Void and Sanctuary Realm, casting Night Raid - Halt grants 30 Heartflow. In Epiphany Realm, Base DMG of Thunder Outflux - Night Raid and Thunder Outflux - Mirror Return increases by 50%.",
          "notes": "",
