          "memory": "Build:Vergil",
          "bio": "A legendary devil swordsman who masters lightning-fast quick-draw techniques. The elder twin of Dante.",
          "effect": "<strong>Judgment Cut – [blue]With Yamato + Press and Hold Red Orb/Basic Attack/Jump + Release Button[/blue]</strong>\n Casts Judgment Cut after performing the corresponding action, dealing [red]960%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG.\n When Vergil is in SDT Form, Judgment Cut has a bigger range and deals [red]1440%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG. Meanwhile, he can spend up to 3 Devil Souls and restore [red]7 Signature Energy and 5 JCE Points[/red] per Devil Soul consumed.\n - When team has more than 3 Truewill and Vergil is in SDT Form, Judgment Cut will consume [red]3 Truewill[/red], have [red]30%[/red] higher Base DMG, deal fixed [red]600%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG, and restore [red]25 JCE Points[/red].\n - Release the corresponding button when the weapon glows to cast Precise Judgment Cut, up to 3 times. If Vergil is in SDT Form, keep holding Basic Attack to cast Judgment Cut continuously, and consuming Devil Souls is regarded as Precise Judgment Cut. Precise Judgment Cuts can be cast at a faster speed.\n\n<strong>Round Trip – [blue]With Mirage Edge + Press and Hold Blue Orb/Basic Attack/Jump Until Weapon Glows + Release Button[/blue]</strong>\n Throws out Mirage Edge after the corresponding action, dealing [red]520%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG ([red]780%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG when in SDT Form).\n - Casting a Mirage Edge skill after throwing the blade out will call it back in priority.\n\n<strong>Doppelganger</strong>\n In SDT Form, Vergil will launch joint attacks with his Doppelganger. Each joint attack deals [red]160%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG.\n\n<strong>Air Trick – [blue]Ground + Locked-on Enemy + Not Push Joystick + Press and Hold Dodge[/blue]</strong>\n Vergil quickly approaches the locked-on enemy.\n\n<strong>Provocation – [blue]Tap Core Passive Bar[/blue]</strong> \n Vergil taunts the enemy, dealing [red]1%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG.\n\n<strong>Mirage Blades – [blue]Netherworld Arm Not Charged + Tap Netherworld Arm[/blue]</strong>\n Deals [red]2%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG with Mirage Blades.\n - This skill can be cast without any Netherworld Arm equipped.\n\n<strong>Blistering / Heavy Rain Blades – [blue]Netherworld Arm Charged + Push/Not Push Joystick + Tap Netherworld Arm[/blue]</strong>\n Blistering: Deals [red]200%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG ([red]320%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG when carrying Netherworld Arm - Mirage Blades).\n Heavy Rain: Deals [red]200%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG and slows enemy unit down. Deals [red]320%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG when carrying Netherworld Arm - Mirage Blades.\n - Equipping a Netherworld Arm other than mirage Blades will trigger the corresponding active skill.\n\n<strong>Storm / Spiral Blades – [blue]Netherworld Arm Charged + Push/Not Push Joystick + Press and Hold Netherworld Arm[/blue]</strong> \n Storm: Deals [red]200%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG. Deals [red]320%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG when carrying Netherworld Arm - Mirage Blades.\n Spiral: Deals [red]200%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG. Deals [red]320%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG when carrying Netherworld Arm - Mirage Blades.\n - Equipping a Netherworld Arm that is not Mirage Blades will trigger the Netherworld Arm's Active Skill.\n\n<strong>Effect: Ultima Slash</strong> \n Certain skills build up [red]Sharp Reserve[/red]. [red]Sharp Reserve[/red] can be passed on to the next character affected by Ultima Slash effect, up to [red]999[/red] points.\n - When [red]Sharp Reserve[/red] reaches [red]100[/red] points, the next skill with [red]Ultima Slash[/red] effect that hits an enemy will consume [red]100 points of Sharp Reserve[/red] to trigger a [red]Ultima Slash[/red], dealing [red]400%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG.\n - Gains [red]1[/red] point of [red]Truewill[/red] each time it triggers, up to [red]90[/red] points.",
          "priority": "Deals 30% more CRIT DMG. Triggers Matrix if it is not on cooldown when casting Sin Devil Trigger. Doubles the JCE Points acquisition efficiency.",
