          "memory": "Build:Spectre",
          "bio": "Nearly 80% of the Spectre frame's design was done by Teddy herself. She originally based it on the Decryptor frame, aiming to craft a more combat-ready model, just in case. After linking with Elysium's core, the missing components were finally completed.",
          "effect": "<strong>Phonograph Circuit</strong>\nOutside Data Domain, only [red]White Noise Signal Orbs[/red] can be obtained. Inside Data Domain, gains unlimited [red]Brown Signal Orbs[/red]. Orb Slot 1 is fixed as the [red]Neon Orb[/red] slot, and specific Neon Orbs of corresponding colors can be activated during the end lag of casting specific skills. Neon Orbs count as 3-Ping Signal Orbs. While casting Neon Orbs, gains Invincibility.\n- When [red]Raydiance[/red] Effect is selected, Teddy: Spectre is regarded as carrying [red]Exposure Mark[/red].\n\n<strong>Inverted Buffer: [blue]Outside Data Domain + Tap White Noise Signal Orb[/blue]</strong>\nLeaps into the air and launches a mighty descending kick attack on enemies. While ascending, continuously ping Signal Orbs to summon matrix bombardments on enemies. The third ping clears all White Noise Signal Orbs. Becomes Invincible and dodges incoming attacks during ascent. Up to [red]16[/red] White Noise Signal Orbs can be recorded.\n- Each White Noise Signal Orb pinged deals [red]540%[/red] Ice DMG.\n- While descending, the kick attack deals [red]720%[/red] Ice DMG to enemies and activates Red Neon Orb during the end lag. Gains Super Armor and [red]50%[/red] DMG Reduction during descent.\n- When casting [red]Red Neon Orb - Feedforward Activation[/red], deals additional Ice DMG based on the number of White Noise Signal Orbs recorded and restores Signature Energy.\n\n<strong>Mirrorflow Matrix: [blue]Inside Data Domain + Tap Brown Signal Orb[/blue]</strong>\nAttack enemies, pinging up to 3 times consecutively and dealing [red]450% / 700% / 1200%[/red] Ice DMG respectively. Activates [red]Red Neon Orb[/red] during the end lag of the third hit.\n\n<strong>Hacked Mark</strong>\n Colored Neon Orb Skills and [red]Signature - Digital Space: Flash Retention[/red] attacks apply [red]Hacked Mark[/red] to the first target hit for [red]10s[/red]. When hacked targets take DMG, triggers bombardment attacks in the target area. Up to [red]1 Hacked Mark[/red] may exist at the same time. When hacked targets die, [red]Hacked Mark[/red] spreads to a nearby target and has its duration reset.\n- Bombardment attacks deal [red]500%[/red] Ice DMG. [red]Signature - Digital Space: Barrier Rift[/red] detonates marks to deal [red]1000%[/red] Ice DMG to hacked targets.\n- If carrying [red]Exposure Mark[/red], bombardment attacks deal [red]600%[/red] Raydiance DMG instead.\n\n<strong>Analog-Digital Conversion</strong>\nWhen casting Neon Orb Skills inside Data Domain, records the Neon Orb's color and consumes up to [red]1/3[/red] of max Signature Energy. Each color can only be recorded at most once. When pinging Neon Orbs to cast corresponding skills, gains healing equal to [red]10%[/red] ATK. Depending on the number of recorded Neon Orb colors (1 / 2 / 3), deals [red]200% / 400% / 1500%[/red] Ice DMG to enemies.\n\n<strong>Tuned Filter: [blue]Press and hold Dodge / Inside Data Domain+Press and hold Energy Bar[/blue]</strong>\nAfter a successful Dodge, press and hold Dodge to counterattack enemies with [red]250%[/red] Ice DMG. If attacked during this counter while holding Dodge, consumes [red]250[/red] Dodge Gauge and performs another counterattack with [red]250%[/red] Ice DMG.\n- Inside Data Domain, pressing and holding Energy Bar summons bear paws to claw at enemies, dealing [red]200%[/red] Ice DMG. During the end lag, activates a special Neon Orb. Consuming this special Neon Orb deals [red]600%[/red] Ice DMG to enemies, grants [red]90[/red] Signature Energy, and clears the first recorded Neon Orb color.\n\n<strong>Op-Amp Overflow</strong>\nAlly units healed by Teddy: Spectre gain [red]Frost Crystal[/red] effect that increases Ice DMG by [red]20%[/red] and [red]Strobe Photovoltaic[/red] effect that increases Raydiance DMG by [red]22.5%[/red] for [red]8[/red]s. Duration resets every time it is triggered.\n\n<strong>Coupling Interference: [blue]Tap Energy Bar[/blue]</strong>\nSummons bear claws to attack enemies, dealing [red]10% / 15% / 20%[/red] Ice DMG respectively.\n<strong>Effect: Raydiance</strong>\nAccumulates [red]Raydiance Gauge[/red]. When the gauge is full, Bianca can enter [red]Radiant Baptism Form[/red] by casting certain skills and gain [red]10[/red] stacks of [red]Radiant Crown[/red]. Some skills consume [red]Radiant Crown[/red] stacks and grant enhancements while triggering [red]Radiant Embrace[/red] to deal Raydiance DMG.\n- [red]Raydiance Gauge[/red] is capped at [red]1000[/red] points.\n- [red]Radiant Embrace[/red] deals [red]330%[/red] Raydiance DMG.",
          "priority": "ATK increases by 10%. While in Data Domain, Extra DMG Bonus increases by 35%. When Teddy: Spectre casts Signature - Data Domain: Barrier Rift without carrying an Exposure Mark, she gains 1/2/3 background Signature charges based on the number of Neon Orb colors recorded. Each time allies cast their Signature Move, she gains 75 Signature Energy, up to three times. When switched in, if there is sufficient Signature Energy, she automatically casts Data Domain: New Dimension Expansion. If Teddy: Spectre enters battle carrying an Exposure Mark, Extra DMG Bonus of Pulse Noise Penetration increases by 100%.",
