          "memory": "Build:Arete",
          "bio": "The ultimate Amalgamator, codenamed \"Malkuth.\" Full activation requires an Amalgamation array built with mechanical units such as bionic whales. The frame can freely switch between human and centaur forms to deliver attacks beyond power limits.",
          "effect": "<strong>Mimicry Armor</strong>\nArete can only use White Signal Orbs. Basic Attacks in [red]Forest Guard Mimic[/red] and [red]Nessos Mimic[/red] only generate White Signal Orbs.\n - When Arete is in [red]Forest Guard Mimic[/red] or [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], tap Red Orb to switch to [red]Crusher Module[/red] or press and hold Red Orb to directly cast the 2nd hit and switch to [red]Crusher Module[/red]; tap Yellow Orb to switch to [red]Breacher Module[/red] or press and hold Yellow Orb to directly cast the 2nd hit and switch to [red]Breacher Module[/red]; tap Blue Orb to switch to [red]Piercer Module[/red] or press and hold Blue Orb to directly cast the 2nd hit and switch to [red]Piercer Module[/red].\n- When Arete is in [red]Forest Guard Mimic[/red], pinging White Signal Orbs grants up to [red]60 Light Links[/red], and consuming [red]Light Links[/red] grants up to [red]2 Grayscale Links[/red].\n- When Arete switches to [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], consuming [red]Grayscale Link[/red] grants up to [red]60 Overridden Blessing[/red].\n- When Arete is in [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], has Super Armor for the whole duration.\n- When switching forms, unconsumed [red]Light Link[/red], [red]Overridden Blessing[/red], and White Signal Orbs are retained.\n\n<strong>Dark Imbue</strong>\nWhen Arete deals DMG in [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], she also weakens the enemy.\n- Applies [red]Chain Fusion[/red] that reduces the enemy's Dark Resistance by [red]25%[/red] for [red]2s[/red].\n\n<strong>Potential Energy Unit</strong>\nWhen Arete is in [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], Signature Energy can only be gained by consuming [red]Overridden Blessing[/red].\n- Each [red]1 Overridden Blessing[/red] consumed increases [red]Signature - Omniversal Step's[/red] Base DMG by [red]0.75%[/red], up to [red]45%[/red]. This effect resets after she casts Signature Move.\n\n<strong>Momentum Execution</strong>\nWhen the team carries [red]Ultima Slash[/red] effect, Arete gains [red]5 Sharp Reserve[/red] per [red]2 Light Links[/red] consumed in [red]Forest Guard Mimic[/red] and triggers Ultima Slash per [red]6 Overridden Blessing[/red] consumed in [red]Nessos Mimic[/red].\n\n<strong>Twin Rotation: [blue]Tap/Press and Hold Morph Orb[/blue]</strong>\nWhen Arete switches to [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], every [red]1 Grayscale Link[/red] held grants [red]30 Overridden Blessing[/red] and removes both current [red]Grayscale Links[/red]. Switching forms when having [red]2 Grayscale Links[/red] triggers active Matrix.\n- When switching to [red]Nessos Mimic[/red] with [red]1 / 2 Grayscale Links[/red] held, deals [red]5000% / 10000%[/red] Dark DMG. When the team carries [red]Ultima Slash[/red] effect, deals [red]2400% / 4800%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG instead.\n- During the first form switch in each battle, the camera focuses on Arete triggering the [red]Ephemeral Flash[/red] animation. Subsequently, press and hold Morph Orb to trigger the [red]Ephemeral Flash[/red] animation; tap Morph Orb to trigger the [red]Shadow Reversion[/red] animation. Modules can be switched during form switch animations.\n- When having [red]2 Grayscale Links[/red] and triggering [red]Shadow Reversion[/red] animation for quick switch to [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], triggers [red]Time Lag Calculation[/red]. When having [red]2 Grayscale Links[/red] for the first time in the battle and triggering [red]Ephemeral Flash[/red] animation for quick switch to [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], triggers [red]Time Lag Calculation[/red].\n- When having [red]2 same-colored Grayscale Links[/red], can consume [red]30 Signature Energy[/red] to gain [red]Sin Engraving[/red] that increases Dark DMG by [red]20%[/red]. [red]Sin Engraving[/red] is removed after casting [red]Signature - Omniversal Step[/red] or exiting [red]Nessos Mimic[/red]. When the team carries [red]Ultima Slash[/red] effect, [red]Sin Engraving[/red] increases Ultima Slash DMG by [red]20%[/red] instead.\n- When the team carries [red]Ultima Slash[/red] effect, switching forms without [red]Grayscale Link[/red] allows consuming [red]5 Signature Energy[/red] to deal [red]200%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG. On hit, can [red]trigger Ultima Slash[/red]. When having [red]2 same-colored Grayscale Links[/red] and switching to [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], gains [red]Field Mark[/red]. [red]Field Mark[/red] is removed after casting [red]the Field-marked Signature - Omniversal Step[/red], or upon switching to [red]Nessos Mimic[/red] with [red]2 different-colored Grayscale Links[/red].\n\n<strong>Chaotic Protocol: [blue]Forest Guard Mimic + Tap Special Orb[/blue]</strong>\n\nWhen Arete is in [red]Forest Guard Mimic[/red], the combo sequences of [red]Crusher Module[/red], [red]Breacher Module[/red], and [red]Piercer Module[/red] are changed.\n\n<strong>Amalgam Dodge</strong>\nWhen Arete is in [red]Forest Guard Mimic[/red] or [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], Dodge prioritizes consuming [red]Amalgam Dodge Gauge[/red]. [red]Amalgam Dodge Gauge[/red] naturally regenerates while in [red]Forest Guard Mimic[/red] or [red]Nessos Mimic[/red], and consuming [red]Overridden Blessing[/red] grants a large amount of [red]Amalgam Dodge Gauge[/red].\n- When [red]Amalgam Dodge Gauge[/red] reaches maximum, taking DMG during skills consumes all [red]Amalgam Dodge Gauge[/red] to negate that instance of DMG and grants Super Armor and [red]100%[/red] DMG Reduction for [red]1s[/red].\n\n<strong>Effect: Ultima Slash</strong>\nCertain skills build up [red]Sharp Reserve[/red]. [red]Sharp Reserve[/red] can be passed on to the next character affected by [red]Ultima Slash[/red] effect, up to [red]999[/red] points.\n- When [red]Sharp Reserve[/red] reaches [red]100[/red] points, the next skill with [red]Ultima Slash[/red] effect that hits an enemy will consume [red]100[/red] points of [red]Sharp Reserve[/red] to trigger a [red]Ultima Slash[/red], dealing [red]400%[/red] Ultima Slash DMG.\n- Gains 1 point of [red]Truewill[/red] each time it triggers, up to [red]90[/red] points.",
          "priority": "ATK increases by 10%. Base DMG of Twin Rotation increases by 100%. Sin Engraving's DMG boost increases by 50%.",
