          "memory": "Build:Dirge",
          "bio": "An Amplifier frame independently developed by the Science Council. Optimized for indoor combat, it features high-efficiency data modules that process and analyze battlefield intel in real time across wide areas.",
          "effect": "<strong>Night Severed</strong>\nWhile in normal form, only Blue Orbs can be used, and basic attacks only generate Blue Orbs. While in [red]Bloodhunter Form[/red], only Red Orbs can be used, and basic attacks only generate Red Orbs\n- When entering [red]Bloodhunter Form[/red], remaining Blue Orbs will be converted to Red Orbs.\n- When switching from [red]Bloodhunter Form[/red] to normal form, remaining Red Orbs will be convereted to Blue Orbs.\n\n'''Raven's Oath: [blue]Press and Hold Dodge[/blue]<strong>\nTransforms into two birds, spinning forward in a dash, then enters [red]Ravenborn Form[/red]. While in Ravenborn Form, increases Movement Speed, gains Super Armor, and continuously charges energy. Each collision with enemies while in Ravenborn Form deals damage.\n- While in [red]Ravenborn Form[/red], each collision with enemies deals [red]20%[/red] Nihil DMG.\n\n</strong>Death Stroke: [blue]Ravenborn Form + Release Dodge when energy/Blue Orbs are insufficient[/blue]<strong>\nExits Ravenborn Form and slashes, dealing [red]90%[/red] Nihil DMG\n\n</strong>Nether Blade: [blue]In Ravenborn Form + Release Dodge when fully charged + Blue Orbs ≥ 1[/blue]<strong>\nExits Ravenborn Form and delivers a powerful slash, pinging up to 3 Blue Orbs to deal Nihil DMG based on the number of orbs pinged while gaining [red]Omen Points[/red] and [red]Signature Energy[/red].\n- Deals [red]120% / 240% / 360%[/red] Nihil DMG in total and gains [red]40 / 80 / 120 Omen Points[/red] and [red]8 / 16 / 24 Signature Energy[/red] based on the number of orbs pinged.\n\n</strong>Deathbreak<strong>\nAllied units healed by Nirvatia gain a boost. If all members are Nihil characters, they gain an additional Flock effect. When casting [red]Raven Ritual[/red], [red]Fatal Kiss[/red], or [red]Hanging Phantom[/red], Nirvatia immediately heals herself for HP equal to 10% of her ATK.\n- Allied units healed by Nirvatia gain a [red]Void Collapse[/red] effect, which increases Nihil DMG by [red]20%[/red] for [red]8[/red]s. Duration resets every time it is triggered.\n\n</strong>Flock<strong>\nIf all members are Nihil characters, the [red]Void Collapse[/red] effect applied by Dirge is further enhanced by [red]15%[/red].\n\n</strong>Amalgam Dodge'''\nWhile in [red]Bloodhunter Form[/red], Nirvatia Dirge's Base DMG efficiency against Equilibrium Field increases by 100%.",
