          "memory": "Build:Aeternion",
          "bio": "A new frame incorporating the latest breakthrough in Corona Gene research. Its output, response speed, and other combat-related specs have all been enhanced. Kamui's own takeaway, though, is that he seems to have gotten a little better at video games.",
          "effect": "<strong>Output Discharge</strong>\nAeternion enters the battlefield wielding a [red]Charge Form[/red] greatsword. When the weapon is in [red]Charge Form[/red], Aeternion can only use Blue or Yellow Orbs, and basic attacks can only generate Blue Orbs. When the weapon switches to [red]Discharge Form[/red], he can only use Red or Yellow Orbs, and basic attacks can only generate Red Orbs. When the weapon is in [red]Charge Form[/red], [red]Output[/red] is capped at [red]60[/red]. When the weapon switches to [red]Discharge Form[/red], the [red]Output[/red] cap increases to [red]90[/red].\n\n<strong>Incandescence</strong>\nWhen Aeternion is switched in, triggers Matrix if it is not on cooldown.\n\n<strong>Thunder Haze</strong>\nWhen Aeternion deals DMG using the [red]Discharge Form[/red] greatsword, enemies will be weakened.\n- Applies a [red]Scorching Invasion[/red] effect to enemies, reducing their Fire Resistance by [red]25%[/red] for [red]2s[/red].\n- When dealing DMG, if the team has the Plasma Beam effect, applies a [red]Coiled Tempest[/red] effect to enemies, reducing their Plasma Beam Resistance by [red]25%[/red] for [red]2s[/red].\n\n<strong>Crown Arc: [blue]Wielding Discharge Form Greatsword + Press and Hold Dodge[/blue]</strong>\nSwings the greatsword upward with full force and jumps up, dealing [red]1800%[/red] Fire DMG. When Aeternion is airborne, performs a powerful downward slash and a thrusting sweep in front, dealing [red]1708%[/red] Fire DMG. Gains Super Armor and Invincible when casting.\n- When Electric Storm Flash is active, or when Electric Storm Flash is not active but the character has [red]Voltaic marks[/red], consumes 1 mark, dealing [red]1764% / 1676%[/red] Plasma Beam DMG instead of Fire DMG.\n- When casting with at least 90 Output, clears [red]Output[/red]. Every [red]1 Output[/red] converts to [red]1 Flare Point[/red], and the DMG of Crown Arc is increased to 5 times its original value. Also gains [red]60 Signature Energy[/red], refreshes Matrix cooldown, and triggers 1 active Matrix.\n\n<strong>Solar Flux</strong>\nWhen team members exit Electric Storm Flash state, Aeternion gains [red]3 Voltaic marks[/red]. When Aeternion is not in Electric Storm Flash state, [red]1 Voltaic mark[/red] can be consumed to make [red]Crown Arc[/red], [red]Ignited Radiance[/red], and [red]Molten Heart[/red] deal Plasma Beam DMG instead of Fire DMG.\n\n<strong>Radiant Expulsion: [blue]Tap Dodge[/blue]</strong>\nPush the joystick and tap Dodge to charge forward with shield raised, dealing [red]200%[/red] Fire DMG to enemies. When Aeternion wields the [red]greatsword in Charge Form[/red], tap Dodge without pushing the joystick. If attacked by enemies during this time, becomes immune to the damage and immediately counters with a shield rush, dealing [red]400%[/red] Fire DMG to enemies.\n\n<strong>Energized Barrier</strong><brAfter casting [red]Solar Poise[/red] and [red]Fusion Slash[/red], Aeternion gains a shield equal to [red]40%[/red] of max HP.\n\n<strong>Effect: Plasma Beam</strong>\n\nEffect Charging: Electric Charge is capped at 1000.\n- Effect Activated: Character with the Plasma Beam Effect enters the Electric Storm Flash status, launching lightning bolt strikes at nearby enemies every 2s and dealing [red]800%[/red] Plasma Beam DMG (without triggering Tank and Breaker Class Skills) for 12s.",
          "priority": "ATK increases by 10%. Base DMG of Signature - Molten Heart doubles. Casting Signature - Molten Heart grants 3 Signal Orbs. This effect can trigger at most twice each time Aeternion enters the battlefield.",
